The paper deals with the problem of estimating the rate-distortion function of an unknown source from empirical data, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the behavior of the plug-in estimator, which is a common method in machine learning and statistics (cs.LG). The analysis of the performance of the estimator is complicated by the fact that the rate-distortion function is not continuous, which is a topic in mathematical analysis and topology (cs.DS). The paper also mentions lossy data compression, which is a topic in multimedia (cs.MM), and discusses the estimation of the optimal reproduction distribution, which is a topic in signal processing and information theory (cs.SI).
